cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper discusses access control and security issues in the Tor network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed framework also involves data structures (cs.DS) and system design (cs.SY) to enforce access policies. Finally, the implementation and evaluation of the framework require software engineering techniques (cs.SE).
